│ THOUGHT: Now I can see the issue. The `isSingleSourceMaskImpl` function     │
│ assumes that all mask elements are either -1 (undef) or valid indices, but  │
│ it doesn't handle poison values. In LLVM IR, poison values in shuffle masks │
│ are represented as special values that should be treated similarly to undef │
│ (-1). The problem is that when the shuffle mask contains poison, it gets    │
│ converted to some invalid integer value that triggers the assertion. I need │
│ to check how poison values are represented in shuffle masks and add proper  │
│ handling for them before the bounds check.                                  │
